edu.usc.scrc.PriorityPruner
Class SnpInfo

java.lang.Object
  edu.usc.scrc.PriorityPruner.SnpInfo
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<SnpInfo>
public class SnpInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<SnpInfo>

This class stores information about a certain SNP. When information from the tped and SNP input file is matched, an object of this class will be stored in a SnpGenotypes-object, which stores all information about a single SNP.

SnpInfo

public SnpInfo(java.lang.String snpName,
               java.lang.String chr,
               int pos,
               java.lang.String allele1,
               java.lang.String allele2,
               double pValue,
               int numAssays,
               boolean forceInclude,
               double[] metrics)
        throws PriorityPrunerException
Constructor for SnpInfo. Makes quick checks to determine if this SNP has passed the design score minimum and if it's pseudo autosomal or not.

Parameters:
snpName - name of this SNP
chr - chromosome of this SNP
pos - base pair position
allele1 - first allele
allele2 - second allele
pValue - associated p-value
numAssays - associated number of bead types as defined in SNP input file
forceInclude - flag showing whether or not to force include this SNP
metrics - metric weights defined for this SNP in SNP input file
Throws:
PriorityPrunerException - if unable to retrieve data from CommandLineOptions
Method Detail

compareTo

public int compareTo(SnpInfo obj)
Allows sorting of SnpInfo-objects, by ascending p-values. Implements comparison by SNP name in case p-value is the same.

addTaggedBy

public void addTaggedBy(SnpInfo snpInfo,
                        double rSquared)
Allows the storing of a SNP that has tagged this SNP, and the associated r^2 value. In cases where the SNP is tagged by a surrogate and the r^2 value is unknown, "-1" is entered (in Pruner).

Parameters:
snpInfo - the SNP tagging this SNP
rSquared - associated r^2 value
